data.title: Bitcoin, Ethereum, Dogecoin, XRP dip as crypto liquidations exceed $1B; BTC at $109,886.40, ETH at $3,854.81. Market volume up 16%, $1B liquidated in 24hrs. DOMINANCE: BTC 60%, ETH 12.6%. EVAPORATED: $950M in long positions. RISK: $580M in BTC shorts.
data.description: Cryptocurrency prices plummeted with stocks as investors remained unenthusiastic about the U.S.-China trade truce. As of 9:25 p.m. ET, Bitcoin dropped by 0.47% to $109,886.40, Ethereum fell by 1.51% to $3,854.81, XRP decreased by 3.40% to $2.47, Solana was down by 3.88% to $186.51, and Dogecoin declined by 3.70% to $0.1853. Bitcoin hit an intraday low of $106,376.69, with a 16% increase in trading volume. Ethereum briefly went below $3,700 but recovered some losses. XRP and Solana fell over 3%, with Bitcoin dominating 60% market share and Ethereum at 12.6%. Over $1 billion was liquidated from the market, $950 million from long positions. Bitcoin shorts risk $580 million liquidation if it rebounds to $117,000. Bitcoin's open interest dropped by 2.42% in the last 24 hours. full story on Benzinga.com.

data.title: Bitcoin ETFs report $470M outflow in the US, ending 4-day inflow streak. Investors react to market and Fed signals.
data.description: Bitcoin ETFs in the United States saw a significant shift in investor behavior, with a withdrawal of $470 million recorded after four consecutive days of inflows. This change came as investors responded to current market conditions and signals from the Federal Reserve.

data.title: HK Monetary Authority opens tender for HK$2.25 billion 3-year institutional govt bonds, settling on Nov 6, 2025.
data.description: The Hong Kong Monetary Authority has issued a tender to reopen 3-year HKD HKSAR Institutional Government Bonds. An offering of HK$2.25 billion will be made, and the settlement is scheduled for November 6, 2025.
